<L>__{exterior country road, ct. early morning}
<A>__{pilgrim is first to find his legs. judith's horse, its leg broken at the ankle, walks in a confused state. judith's foot is helplessly caught in the stirrup...}
<C>__{grace }
<D>__{... judith's foot was caught in the stirrup... she couldn't get up, she was so scared...}
<P>__{(cries)}
<D>__{i saw this truck, coming around the turn...}
<A>__{she sees the glint of the steel. the truck suddenly appears from around the bend.}
<C>__{grace }
<D>__{...he was honking, trying to get us to move... i tried to grab the reins to get judith's horse out of the way...}
<A>__{grace grabs the reins of judith's horse. the horses are spooking...}
<C>__{grace }
<D>__{...and the truck started skidding...}
<A>__{the truck skidded on the icy road, going out of control, jack knifing, heading right for them...}
<C>__{grace }
<D>__{...it was coming right at us... there wasn't any time to do anything... it ran right into judith's horse...}
<A>__{the truck bed plows into judith's horse...}
<C>__{grace }
<D>__{...judith just disappeared... and it came right at pilgrim and me...}
<A>__{we see this...}
<C>__{grace }
<D>__{...and pilgrim reared up at the truck and i fell off...}
<A>__{grace falls onto the road, the truck running over her.}
